# Common Rules — Limerence Workspace

Applies to **mobile** and **web**. Stack-specific patterns stay in `mobile.mdc` / `web.mdc`.

## Code Style (shared)

- Functional components only; **named exports** (no default exports for new code)
- Prefer `interface` over `type`; avoid `enum` (use union types or `as const`)
- File order: component → subcomponents → helpers → constants → types
- Folders: `kebab-case`; components: `PascalCase`; booleans: `is/has/can` prefix
- Structured logging: `console.log({ event: 'Service.method', id })`
- Prefer early returns; avoid deep nesting
- Co-locate tests in `__tests__/` next to source
- Pure logic in `utils/` / `mappers/` — unit testable, no React in pure helpers
- Types: dedicated `types/` or `services/dto/` — UI must not import raw DB shapes without mappers

| Concern | Mobile | Web |
|---------|--------|-----|
| Styling | `StyleSheet` + `theme.ts` — see `mobile.mdc` | Tailwind — see `web.mdc` |
| State | Redux Toolkit — see `mobile.mdc` | Zustand — see `web.mdc` |
| Data layer | Service → Manager → Repository | `*Service.ts` + mappers |

## Comments — preserve, don't delete

Preserving existing documentation has **higher priority** than cleanup.

**Never remove (unless behavior was deleted):** file-level JSDoc, `@see docs/...`, field docs, «why» comments, section markers, still-relevant `eslint-disable`.

**Safe to remove:** stale TODOs, changelog noise, comments that verbatim duplicate the next line, dead commented-out code.

When refactoring — **migrate** comments to the new symbol/file, don't drop them.

## Symbol documentation — required

Every **exported** symbol and every **module-level** binding must have a JSDoc description (one line minimum).

**Human-readable:** пиши для человека, который впервые открывает файл — полными фразами, простым языком. Объясняй **зачем** символ существует и **как** используется, а не пересказывай имя типа или сигнатуру.

| Do | Don't |
|----|-------|
| «Настройки монетизации истории с сервера — какие tier keys показывать в paywall» | «RPC response DTO config» |
| «Общий репозиторий: entitlements, purchase intents, вызовы Supabase RPC» | «Shared repo entitlements intents RPC» |
| «null — автор не включил покупку всей истории» | «null = not configured» |

Язык: **русский** для domain/бизнес-смысла; `@file` / `@see` — как в соседних файлах модуля. Идентификаторы кода (`tierKey`, RPC-имена) — в backticks внутри текста.

| Symbol | Required docs |
|--------|----------------|
| **Class** | Зачем класс; публичные методы — что делают, когда из имени неочевидно |
| **Function / method** | Что делает и в каком flow; `@param` / `@returns` — если сигнатуры мало |
| **Type / interface / model** | Что означает в продукте, откуда данные; неочевидные поля — отдельный JSDoc |
| **Const / global / singleton export** | Что хранит, кто читает, живёт ли кэш / singleton на весь app |
| **File** (non-trivial modules) | `@file` + `@description`; `@see docs/...` при связи со spec |

**Non-exported** symbols: JSDoc when purpose, constraints, or side effects are not obvious from the name.

**Refactor rule:** touching a symbol without docs → add docs in the same change. Never strip docs «for cleanup».

```ts
// ❌ Нет описания
export type StoryMonetizationConfigDTO = { storyId: string };

// ❌ Телеграф — не для человека
/** RPC get_player_monetization_config DTO tier keys paywall */

// ✅ Человекочитаемо + ссылка на spec
/**
 * Настройки монетизации истории с сервера: tier keys для paywall и early access по главам.
 * Только released chapters. Кэшируется в MonetizationConfigService.
 * @see docs/monetization/STORE_CATALOG.md
 */
export type StoryMonetizationConfigDTO = {
  /** Ключ ценовой ступени «полный доступ»; null — автор не продаёт историю целиком. */
  fullStoryTierKey: string | null;
};

// ❌ Module singleton без описания
export const monetizationRepository = new MonetizationRepository();

// ✅
/** Единый доступ к Supabase monetization: entitlements, intents, complete_purchase. */
export const monetizationRepository = new MonetizationRepository();
```

## Spec before code

**Source of truth:** `docs/specs/` and `docs/monetization/`. See `documentation.mdc` for layers and paths.

1. Read relevant spec before coding
2. Update spec if behavior changes (same task as code)
3. Implement with `@see docs/specs/...` or `@see docs/monetization/...`
4. Remove code paths not in spec

### Entity index

| Entity | Spec |
|--------|------|
| Dialog | `docs/specs/gameplay/entities/Диалог.md` |
| Scene | `docs/specs/gameplay/entities/Сцена.md` |
| Chapter | `docs/specs/gameplay/entities/Глава.md` |
| Character | `docs/specs/gameplay/entities/Персонаж.md` |
| Dialog frame | `docs/specs/gameplay/entities/РамкаДиалога.md` |
| Paywall BR | `docs/specs/monetization/paywall.md` |
| Entitlements | `docs/monetization/ENTITLEMENTS.md` |
| Analytics events | `docs/specs/analytics-events.md` |
| Tech architecture | `docs/specs/tech-architecture.md` |

## No Legacy — Spec Is the Contract

**Do not preserve legacy code for backward compatibility.** If behavior is outdated, duplicated, or cannot be traced to `docs/specs/` (or `docs/specs/tech-architecture.md` for architecture) — **remove it**. No feature flags or «just in case» branches.

**Safe deletion rule:** logic may be removed only when it is **not** described in docs. Every new or changed business rule must be documented **before or together with** the code change.

| Situation | Action |
|-----------|--------|
| Code has no spec reference and purpose is unclear | Delete (or stop and ask — do not guess and keep) |
| Code contradicts current spec | Update code to match spec; delete the old path |
| Intentional behavior change | Update spec first or in the same PR, then change code |
| Refactor touching gameplay/product | Verify spec covers all branches; extend spec if a branch was only in code |

Do **not** add `@deprecated` shims, parallel code paths, or «fallback for old behavior» unless the spec explicitly requires transitional behavior.

### Shared anti-patterns

```ts
// ❌ Legacy branch «на всякий случай»
if (useLegacyDialogFrame) { ... } else { ... }

// ✅ One implementation in spec; old path removed

// ❌ Undocumented business logic «пока оставим»
function mysteryReplicaSkip() { ... }

// ✅ Rule in docs/specs → @see in code → test pure logic

// ❌ Default export for new components
export default function SceneScreen() {}

// ✅ Named export
export function SceneScreen() {}
```
